\begin_inset Formula $R\slash sI$
\end_inset

) over 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

.
 In particular, note that
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{alignat*}{3}
\widetilde{E}_{i} & =\begin{cases}
sE_{1} & \text{if }i=1\\
E_{i} & \text{if }i\neq1
\end{cases} & \qquad & \text{and} & \qquad & \widetilde{F}_{i}=\begin{cases}
sF_{1} & \text{if }i=1\\
F_{i} & \text{if }i\neq1
\end{cases}
\end{alignat*}

\end_inset

